  "text": "The heartbeat session timeout mechanism in Apache Kafka works through a multi-layer process that monitors consumer group membership and removes members when they stop sending heartbeats.\n\n## Configuration Definition\nThe heartbeat session timeout threshold is defined through the configuration parameter `SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG` in `CommonClientConfigs.java`. This configuration is extracted into `GroupRebalanceConfig.java` (line 41) which stores the `sessionTimeoutMs` value (line 52).\n\n## Client-Side Timeout Detection\nOn the consumer client side, the `Heartbeat.java` class manages heartbeat timing. The `sessionTimeoutExpired()` method (lines 119-122) checks whether the session timer has expired by calling `sessionTimer.isExpired()`. This method is invoked during the consumer polling loop in the heartbeat thread.\n\nThe heartbeat timeout check occurs in `AbstractCoordinator.java` within the `HeartbeatThread.run()` method (lines 1513-1517). When `heartbeat.sessionTimeoutExpired(now)` returns true, the client marks the coordinator as unknown with the message \"session timed out without receiving a heartbeat response\". This causes the consumer group membership to drop as the client can no longer communicate with the group coordinator.\n\n## Server-Side Timeout Handling\nOn the broker/group coordinator side, `GroupMetadataManager.java` implements `expireClassicGroupMemberHeartbeat()` (lines 6664-6702) which is invoked when a member's heartbeat session timeout expires. This method removes the member from the group and logs: \"Member {memberId} in group {groupId} has failed, removing it from the group\" (lines 6691-6692) or \"Pending member {memberId} in group {groupId} has been removed after session timeout expiration\" (lines 6682-6683).\n\n## Call Chain\nThe complete flow is:\n1. `Heartbeat.sessionTimeoutExpired()` detects the timeout on the client side\n2. `AbstractCoordinator.HeartbeatThread.run()` detects this and calls `markCoordinatorUnknown()`\n3. The consumer drops group membership\n4. Server-side: `GroupMetadataManager.expireClassicGroupMemberHeartbeat()` removes the member and triggers rebalancing\n\nThe timeout value is controlled by the `session.timeout.ms` configuration (default 10 seconds), which must be set according to broker constraints defined by `group.min.session.timeout.ms` and `group.max.session.timeout.ms`."
